Sridevi/Anusha/Vinay,  can u take a look at this ?
Please rename the function: Create A Dictionary With Sensor Name And Service Path URI
I didn't see any value being updated for this list.

sometimes some sensors dbus uri won't be under sensor tree and we also don't know that whether that sensor should gets listed in that subtree only or it should gets listed under sensor tree. so if any sensor which was not showing under sensor tree will be appended to that list.
Check Sensor Reading Value Is Available In Redfish
just a thought, instead of 'As'  'if' or 'is' is more appropriate
Suite setup function is very big.. can u mention in comments what are u trying to do... for reference..
Need Redfish login for this suite.
Please create separate keywords based on the individual functionality for these and call them here.
Description of Arguments required. Add wherever applicable.
lets re-name the dictionary to more meaningful name.
I didn't get the purpose of this dictionary. Also how does this value sync with the values that you are putting to the same dict below. Can you add few comments and give examples to explain.
As Anusha mentioned, please add sample examples to elaborate the purpose of this dictionary.
Validate Redfish Reading And Threshold Value And Sensor State
can u please mention these info in [Documentation] and just have the keyword name  as 'Validate Sensor State For Lower Threshold Values'
can u please mention these info in [Documentation] and just have the keyword name  as 'Validate Sensor State For Upper Threshold Values'
can we club the Health state and reading values into a single function?

Simply 

Open BMC server model should be declared in resource.robot
description is not present for all the api's in this lib file.. please add it.

Instead of saying dot can we say decimal format?

Reading value is in decimal format.
e.g: 10.34

Value before dot is considered as an integer reading value and after dot is considered as fractional reading value.

is of size

change 16bytes to 16 bytes.. where ever applicable
If sensor name is more than 16 bytes then truncate sensor name to 16 bytes  and return decoded sensor name else return the decoded sensor name as it is.
I observe that there is no try and catch block for exception handling.. how to handle in case of failures?

try-catch block is needed in this python function. actually this python function  will get input from "Validate Default Threshold Values Alignment As Per IPMI Spec" keyword which was present on sensor_info_record.robot file. 
Actually in that keyword before passing to the python function we will check how many threshold values are present for an sensor and if it was 1 we can't compare hence we will ignore there itself and if it was more that 1 then we will pass those values to the respective python function and this python function was called with run keyword and continue on failure robot keyword. hence eventhough value comparison failed it will continue to validate to other sensor threshold values.
Two minor comments please fix it.. otherwise +1 from me.
can u mention the documentation for this library?? what is this library for ?
can we please have more appropriate names for lists
Minimum one line space after keyword section.
